OL,3,C'We've escaped from hell': The town at
OL,4,Cthe centre of fighting in Ukraine
OL,6,F"The body of my husband is lying over
OL,7,Fthere," she points down road. "So is
OL,8,Fmy godmother. I'm leaving, and they're
OL,9,Flying there unburied. It's hell."
OL,11,FThey were killed trying to leave the
OL,12,Ftown before the weekend, but no one
OL,13,Fdares to remove their corpses.
OL,15,FNo more than five minutes, and we're
OL,16,Ftold to leave, as it's too dangerous
OL,17,Fto stay. Our exit across the fields is
OL,18,Fas fast as our entry.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G3/6
