OL,3,C'We've escaped from hell': The town at
OL,4,Cthe centre of fighting in Ukraine
OL,6,FWe arrive at a meeting point, still
OL,7,Fwell within range of Russian guns.
OL,8,FThere is a great deal of artillery
OL,9,Ffire, unnervingly close.
OL,11,FMychola Migushenko is an elderly man
OL,12,Fwith a filthy makeshift bandage
OL,13,Fwrapped around his foot. He's lost his
OL,14,Ftoes and a part of his finger. They
OL,15,Fare by no means the deepest scars he
OL,16,Fbears.
OL,18,F"There was a rocket into the house. My
OL,19,Fwife was killed," he says, producing
OL,20,Fher passport to show me her photograph.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G4/6
